{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pizza base","content":["Line a pizza tray or baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside. Grease a bowl with oil and set aside.","Place a jug onto mixing bowl lid and weigh water into it. Add yeast and set aside.","Place all remaining pizza base ingredients into mixing bowl and blend <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>, until mixture resembles fine crumbs.","Add yeast mixture and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>, until combined. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl to loosen dough, then transfer into prepared bowl and set aside to prove for 1 hour (mixture will be quite wet, but will become firmer after proving). Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Coriander pesto","content":["Place garlic, coriander, cashews, sunflower seeds and pepitas into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and blend <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add lemon juice, oil, salt and dulse flakes (optional) and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into a sealable container and place into refrigerator until ready to use. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Toppings","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C.","Place Parmesan into mixing bowl and grate <b>4 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Using damp hands, spread dough mixture onto prepared tray into a circle (approx. 24 cm). Bake for 10 minutes (180°C) or until mixture is lightly browned.","Spread 2½ tablespoons of reserved Coriander pesto to edges of the pizza base. Sprinkle grated Parmesan over pesto and arrange sliced mozzarella, tomatoes and thyme leaves on top. Bake for 10 minutes (180°C) or until cooked to your liking. Allow to cool slightly before slicing and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pizza base","content":["oil, for greasing","200 g lukewarm water","½ tsp dried instant yeast","120 g dried chickpeas","40 g Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)","1 garlic clove","1 sprig fresh rosemary, leaves only","¼ tsp salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","1 tbsp psyllium husk"]},{"title":"Coriander pesto","content":["1 garlic clove","45 g fresh coriander, stalks and leaves cut into pieces (approx. 1½ bunches)","50 g raw unsalted cashews","40 g sunflower seeds","10 g pepitas","40 g lemon juice (approx. 1 lemon)","100 g avocado oil","¼ tsp salt, to taste","1 tsp dulse flakes (optional)"]},{"title":"Toppings","content":["20 g Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)","50 g mozzarella cheese, cut into slices","2 - 4 fresh tomatoes, cut into slices","fresh thyme leaves, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r147933","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-hmtec7L7gvk\/XZVPS1J5NMI\/AAAAAAAAc3E\/XGWUGGVJZegl7G63tCL0bB-wChkntkN4wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_4HW0z-bSWoGCLcqm.png","title":"Coriander pesto pizza","publishedAt":"2018-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"16.6 g","fat":"16.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"7.6 g","calories":"1079 kJ \/ 257 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, bowl, jug, sealable container, pizza tray or baking tray (30 x 40 cm), refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Try using broccoli pesto as an alternative pesto base (Please refer to the <i>Zoodles with broccoli pesto<\/i> recipe on this recipe chip).","For a variety of flavours and colours, we used a tomato medley."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 30m","4 portions"]}